You need two things: a **navigation guard** in `AppShell` and **`BackButtonBehavior`** on the page.

### 1. Guard back navigation in `AppShell.xaml.cs`

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    // Only intercept back (Pop) navigation
    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await Shell.Current.CurrentPage.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

Key points:
- **`GetDeferral()`** is required because `DisplayAlert` is async — without it the navigation completes before the dialog returns.
- **`deferral.Complete()`** must always be called (even after cancel), or navigation locks up.

### 2. Custom "Cancel" back button on `EditProductPage.xaml`

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.EditProductPage">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

### 3. ViewModel command

```csharp
[RelayCommand]
async Task Cancel()
{
    // This triggers a Pop, which hits the OnNavigating guard above
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

The `BackButtonBehavior.Command` replaces the default back-arrow tap, so tapping "Cancel" calls your command, which calls `GoToAsync("..")`, which triggers `OnNavigating` with `ShellNavigationSource.Pop` — the guard dialog appears as expected.

### Expose `HasUnsavedChanges` from the page

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    public bool HasUnsavedChanges { get; set; }
}
```

Set this flag whenever the form is modified (e.g., via a property-changed callback or binding).
